5:
You want me to help as a Guild
receptionist?
8:
Yeah... We've got our hands full with
the Shibuya situation, so we figured
it'd be best to leave you somewhere
else.
11:
...Oh, I see how it is. You don't want to
drag me around because I might
cause trouble again.
16: There you go twisting words again...
19: I'm just saying it the way it is.
24:
Well... You're not entirely wrong, but
that's not the full reason.
26:
We're more worried that someone
with a grudge might target you.
29:
After speaking with Zekhel, we
figured you'd be safest with the
Guild in Palpebra, since not many
people from Shibuya come by.
31:
And... yeah, someone still needs to
keep an eye on you too.
34:
Whatever. It's not like I wanted to
throw hands with those Aegis peeps
in the first place.
38:
Mr. Takamori is doing what he can
as well, so you should be in the clear
soon.
48:
Until then, I'll be looking after you!
You'll be in good hands, promise!
52: Okaaay. Show me the ropes, Lilie.
55:
...Hikawa? Is that you? What are you
doing with the Guild?
58:
Ah, you're the people we were
partnered with back in Shibuya.
61:
Can you guess? I'm working as a
receptionist today!
63:
Huh... If you're helping Lilie, you must
be pretty smart.
66:
What? Anyone can do this. I'm not
doing anything special.
71:
On the contrary! With how fast you
are at calculations, you're a great
help!
77:
Yeah, it's hard to find someone
that's actually thorough with the
paperwork. I swear, everyone
besides the merchants and scholars
have no standards...
84:
Wow, is this how easy it is to be a cut
above the rest in another world?
87:
...Your social skills could use some
work though. Especially that attitude
of yours.
90:
What? Are you really going to take a
stab at my best character trait?
92:
Ahahaha, I actually love that part
about her. Some people need to be
put in their place, y'know?
102:
Do you even need to ask? I can do
anything I put my mind to.
110:
...Just by that? Most of the credit
should go to Lilie since she's picking
the right jobs for me.
115:
I'm just doing what I can to make
sure my favorite newcomer learns
everything from the ground up!
118:
You deserve your fair share of the
credit too for doing such a good job.
121:
Sure, I was a little worried about your
way with words at first, but it turns
out some adventurers actually like it.
124:
Definitely gave me a scare the first
time you called someone "trash"
though...
127:
Excuse me, can I... get some
paperwork done...
131:
Ah, the mage from before. Good
work out there. Just you today?
139:
We made a mistake inside the
Kaleidoscope. He died, while I
survived. That's just... the way life is
for us adventurers.
146:
Hikawa, I'll handle this. If anyone else
comes through the door, can you
help them?
154:
Being an adventurer is very
dangerous, isn't it.
157:
Yeah... Lilie and the Guild are doing
what they can to ease the burden
on them, but there's only so much
they can do.
161:
...Here I was thinking I was so much
better than them...
168:
There's something you want to say
to her, right?
174:
...Maybe, but don't look at me like
that!
179: Thanks, Lilie... I feel a little better now.
181:
I just did what I could... Keep your
chin up, okay? I know it must be
hard, but try not to let it drag you
under.
188: I... I'm not sure how to say this, but...
191:
I had fun talking with you and your
friend.
194:
So don't be a stranger. I'll be waiting
for you to swing by again sometime.
199:
...I liked talking with you too. I know
he did as well.
204:
Stop. Don't come any closer, and
don't you dare look at me.
207: ...I know I've said this before, but...
209:
I also enjoy spending time with you. I
mean it.
